com.vector.cfg.model.state

Interface ICeStatePublished

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IContainerStatePublished, IEcucStatePublished, IHasContainerStatePublished, IModuleConfigurationStatePublished, IParameterStatePublished

    @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
public interface ICeStatePublished
    This interface specifies the published subset of ICeState. It is intended for use in code generator implementations and validations.

    Creation policy

    Instances of related CeState implementations can be created by means of CeStatePublishedFactory.

    Implementation policy

    All published CeState APIs must guarantee that the provided information is static. That's essential because the methods published here may e.g. be used in validation implementations in the code generators. Due to the lack of event support of published CeState APIs dynamic updates of non-static states are not supported. A non-static state for example is ICeState#isChangeable(). A static state for example is the availability of a pre-configuration object since pre-configuration never changes at runtime of the tool.

      • isChangeAllowedAccordingToCurrentConfigurationPhase

        @PublishedMethod
boolean isChangeAllowedAccordingToCurrentConfigurationPhase()
        This method checks if the related object is changeable according to the current configuration phase. No further check are made, so there may be other reasons which deny changing the object (the related ARXML file may be read-only for example).

        What does change mean for containers?

        It means changing immediate attributes of the container like its description text. It doesn't mean creation or deletion of child objects. This has to be checked with the other methods in this interface.
